Like a long arrow through the dark the train is darting, 
A lonely journey, through the night's dark shroud; 
The only sound, the wheels' mournful cloud; 
The train a ghost, a specter of the past, 
A reminder of memories that will forever last. 
The whistle wails, a mournful sigh, 
As the train disappears, into the darkening sky; 
The stars above, a twinkling sea, 
A celestial showcase, for the train to be free. 
With every mile, a memory fades, 
A chapter closed, a story derailed; 
The train a reminder, of love and loss and pain, 
A bittersweet reminder, of life's transient refrain.

Like a long arrow through the dark the train is darting, 
A dreamlike journey, through the night's dark veil; 
The world outside a haze, a watercolor's pale; 
The train a fantasy, a magic carpet's ride, 
A journey through the night, to a world inside. 
The whistle whispers, a gentle hush, 
As the train glides on, with a gentle rush; 
The stars above, a twinkling show, 
A celestial display, for the heart to know. 
With every mile, a dream takes flight, 
A vision of tomorrow, a beacon in the night; 
The train a catalyst, for the heart's desire, 
A journey through the night, to a love that's on fire.
